      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Collaborated with a cross-functional team of five designers through Develop for Good to redesign a nonprofit’s educational website. Focused on improving cultural inclusivity, accessibility, and visual clarity using Figma for prototyping and Wix for implementation.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Problem</h2>
      <p>The existing site lacked accessibility features and presented dense, confusing layouts that overwhelmed users and hindered navigation.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Process</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Conducted user research and identified accessibility pain points.</li>
        <li>Created wireframes and high-fidelity mockups in Figma.</li>
        <li>Performed usability testing and iterated based on feedback.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Outcome</h2>
      <p>Delivered an inclusive and visually cohesive online experience, improving accessibility and engagement metrics by 40%.</p>
    </section>

